18:12.640 --> 18:13.640
The...

18:13.640 --> 18:19.440
In some cases, your figures have been disputed, but assuming that the figures are correct,

18:19.440 --> 18:22.240
eventually what is your committee proposed to do about it?

18:22.240 --> 18:23.440
Well, Mr. Ross, may I...

18:23.440 --> 18:25.440
Oh, may I just lay prices, or how do you...

18:25.440 --> 18:26.440
May I?

18:26.440 --> 18:30.960
May I give you just a brief summary about what our committee has found so far.

18:30.960 --> 18:37.360
We've been studying, of course, the steroid hormones, which is the very wonderful...

18:37.360 --> 18:41.280
And wondered drug is used in the treatment of people who suffer from arthritis,

18:41.280 --> 18:44.440
heart-as-zone and misterivities.

18:44.440 --> 18:47.600
We find the first place that...

18:47.600 --> 18:52.360
That there are prices in England, for instance, says...

18:52.360 --> 18:55.840
Seven cents, seven and a half cents a pill to the drugist.

18:55.840 --> 18:59.280
In this country, almost 18 cents a pill.

18:59.280 --> 19:06.560
We find also that the raw material after being tested and put in tablet form and bottled

19:06.560 --> 19:11.920
at the prices are less than two cents a pill, two cents a tablet, whereas the charge

19:11.920 --> 19:15.920
on almost 18 cents to the drugist.

19:15.920 --> 19:21.160
We find also, since the hearing that we've had that some small companies are actually selling

19:21.160 --> 19:29.320
the drugists, these same pills, which meet USP specifications for less than two cents a

19:29.320 --> 19:30.320
pill.

19:30.880 --> 19:38.400
We find also that the drug industry is the highest in the profit field, considering that worth

19:38.400 --> 19:40.200
of any industry in the United States.

19:40.200 --> 19:43.520
I have a chart here that shows that very graphically.

19:43.520 --> 19:52.080
There's drugs after taxes, about 22 percent, all manufacturing, generally, about 11 percent.

19:52.080 --> 19:58.520
And you will see motor vehicles and soap and petroleum, all of them are very much under

19:58.520 --> 19:59.520
drugs.

19:59.520 --> 20:03.840
And these are medicines that people have to have.

20:03.840 --> 20:07.880
And I also see that in case of shearing and the same is true of up-john and work than

20:07.880 --> 20:15.520
we have had before our committee, but they made enough profits in four years to repay the

20:15.520 --> 20:20.560
net worth of their corporations during those four years.

20:20.560 --> 20:30.200
We find also, strangely enough, that, for instance, in 1959 shearing was bidding to the

20:30.200 --> 20:40.960
government, the M-M-S-A, the Military Medical Supply Agency, for 23 cents a thousand capsules

20:40.960 --> 20:45.680
of pills, whereas they were selling the same to the drugists for $170.

20:45.680 --> 20:48.560
The Senator Keith over the crowd, why that should be?

20:48.560 --> 20:49.560
I don't know.

20:49.560 --> 20:53.800
So I only conclude that I can reach, and the inevitable conclusion is that among these

20:53.800 --> 20:56.320
big companies there just isn't any competition.

20:56.320 --> 20:57.880
They've got their prices way up.

20:57.880 --> 21:05.600
The other thing is that the small companies can are making and selling the same product

21:05.600 --> 21:10.960
for about two and a half or three cents a capsule, whereas the big companies are charging

21:10.960 --> 21:11.960
almost 18.

21:11.960 --> 21:13.400
Senator, if you'll forgive me for pointing it out.

21:13.400 --> 21:14.600
I don't think you answered the question.

21:14.600 --> 21:15.600
I was wrong, Vass.

21:15.600 --> 21:17.320
What are you going to do about it?

21:17.320 --> 21:24.720
The question is too early to say exactly what legislation that we might recommend, but

21:24.720 --> 21:31.960
the harassed doctor with all the detailed information advertising and the medical journals that

21:31.960 --> 21:38.720
he gets is only natural that he wants to prescribe some drug, dealt with that trade name

21:38.720 --> 21:40.440
that he has confidence in.

21:40.440 --> 21:46.200
Well, the government and the veterans' administration has confidence in these little companies, and

21:46.200 --> 21:50.240
they buy them for a thuzard and a water read.

21:50.240 --> 21:54.320
So we must have asked some way so that the government, so that the private position will

21:54.320 --> 21:59.960
have confidence and will be willing to recommend the drugs of these small companies too, then

21:59.960 --> 22:01.680
we'll have real competition.

22:01.680 --> 22:04.520
But you already have government supervision of any drugs of that nature.

22:04.520 --> 22:09.000
Yes, we have the USP standards, and they're standards with teeth in them.

22:09.000 --> 22:18.000
But the medical profession generally feels that they want their physicians to get something

22:18.000 --> 22:21.360
that they're absolutely sure of its efficacy and its quality.

22:21.360 --> 22:26.200
And so, and then they're given a lot of information about these detailed people.

22:26.200 --> 22:32.200
So they use to recommend by the trade name of the high price of the high price.

22:32.200 --> 22:33.680
Would you eliminate the trade name?

22:33.680 --> 22:35.240
No, I wouldn't eliminate the trade name.

22:35.240 --> 22:36.240
And how do you meet the...

22:36.240 --> 22:41.240
Some people, some people have actually recommended that since this is a captive group, that is

22:41.240 --> 22:44.880
the patient is captive, he has no alternative.

22:44.880 --> 22:50.480
He has to take a prescription that the doctor recommends that there ought to be price controls.

22:50.480 --> 22:51.800
I hope you don't have to get to that.

22:51.800 --> 22:57.040
I hope we can find some other method of getting competition and get the prices down, of course,

22:57.040 --> 22:58.440
they certainly ought to come down.

22:58.440 --> 23:04.920
Senator, how do you meet the contention of the pharmaceutical houses that is there independent

23:04.920 --> 23:10.720
research that has developed many of these new drugs and that the profit incentive is what

23:10.720 --> 23:12.600
has spread them to do it?

23:12.600 --> 23:15.040
Do you want to remove the large profit incentive?

23:15.040 --> 23:19.600
No, I want them to have a profit incentive.

23:19.600 --> 23:25.400
But I submit that 22% after taxes is a pretty high profit.

23:25.400 --> 23:29.240
Other manufacturers seem to get along on 11% after taxes generally.

23:29.240 --> 23:30.240
Well, so they've been in the same way.

23:30.240 --> 23:31.720
The situation is this.

23:31.720 --> 23:37.160
So they have done a lot of fine research and I think some of these big drug houses are

23:37.160 --> 23:38.920
fine organizations.

23:38.920 --> 23:41.280
But it just doesn't make sense.

23:41.280 --> 23:48.320
It's upside down economy for them to be selling the pill at almost 18 cents, a tablet almost

23:48.320 --> 23:53.760
18 cents like Pregnant Zone, whereas a small company and many of them do fine research

23:53.760 --> 23:54.760
themselves.

23:54.760 --> 24:01.360
They sell the same pill, tablet, meeting US peace specifications, or less than two cents.

24:01.360 --> 24:06.280
So even if you found in your subcommittee in your opinion that these people are charging

24:06.280 --> 24:09.320
too much and perhaps they're probably not agree with you.

24:09.320 --> 24:13.040
But unless you found evidence of collusion and price fixing, do you think that the Congress

24:13.040 --> 24:15.240
ought to be in the price fixing business?

24:15.240 --> 24:17.840
It's not a matter of fixing prices, Mr. Duffy.

24:17.840 --> 24:24.440
What we are interested in is why does it happen that the prices of these drugs are

24:24.440 --> 24:29.720
really big companies always wind up exactly the same and very, very high.

24:29.720 --> 24:31.680
Why is there no competition?

24:31.680 --> 24:34.400
What can we do to get competition between them?

24:34.400 --> 24:37.480
But you're suggesting that there's some kind of violation of the antitrust laws.

24:37.480 --> 24:40.040
Don't we have a mechanism now established to handle that sort of thing?

24:40.040 --> 24:42.800
Well, the antitrust laws need to be remodeled with great deal.

24:42.800 --> 24:45.520
There's also this additional problem.

24:45.520 --> 24:50.280
The issuance of patents.

24:50.280 --> 24:55.120
We found that in the prednisone, for instance, that five of the big companies were trying

24:55.120 --> 24:59.760
to tie up the market for the future, even though no patent had actually been issued.

24:59.760 --> 25:06.260
So that if a patent is issued, the little companies would have to buy in finished form and

25:06.260 --> 25:10.200
boxes couldn't buy in bulk anymore and they would be put out of business and they'd

25:10.200 --> 25:12.200
be unable to sell with these low prices.

25:12.200 --> 25:16.600
Senator Keith Oliver, a moment ago you made a passing reference to detail men and possibly

25:16.600 --> 25:19.400
some people in our audience aren't aware of what you were talking about.

25:19.400 --> 25:25.240
As I understand it, detail men work for the drug companies such as Murkup, John, Sherring

25:25.240 --> 25:26.240
and so forth.

25:26.240 --> 25:30.880
And it is their job to go to the doctors and explain to the doctors the latest drugs they have,

25:30.880 --> 25:34.120
how they can be used and in some cases even give them samples of it.

25:34.120 --> 25:39.720
Now, we heard testimony before your group that a lot of doctors are appreciative of this

25:39.720 --> 25:41.720
service and they are for the detail men.

25:41.720 --> 25:43.320
Would you do away with the detail men?

25:43.320 --> 25:47.680
I think we still need some detail men, although I think the matter has been carried entirely

25:47.680 --> 25:48.680
too far.

25:48.760 --> 25:55.560
So, in a sense, one third of the price that the drug store pays for the drug goes into

25:55.560 --> 25:59.960
this promotion, this advertisement, 33% and a third percent.

25:59.960 --> 26:01.640
I think that's entirely too much.

26:01.640 --> 26:05.400
We ask a doctor up John, up John and company, how many employees they have.

26:05.400 --> 26:09.240
He said you had about a little more than 5,000.

26:09.240 --> 26:13.720
And he said there had more than 1,000 detail men.

26:13.720 --> 26:18.800
So what I think the physicians would really appreciate would be some authentic and more

26:18.800 --> 26:24.880
public information from the food and drug department on just what these drugs are, what

26:24.880 --> 26:29.800
they'll do, what the side effects are, so that they can have confidence so that they

26:29.800 --> 26:32.640
can know and won't have to rely so much on the detail men.

26:32.640 --> 26:36.760
So I tend to get a little bit back to your home base for just a moment before we have

26:36.760 --> 26:38.360
to close.

26:38.360 --> 26:41.560
